reviews.text: I got the burger with beer cheese and ordered it medium rare. It was cooked perfectly and full of flavor. We also shared the fried onion appetizer and a side of fries, both were great. The chicken chunks were a standout! We tried the honey BBQ and Jamaican jerk sauces, and both were absolutely amazing. Our total was $56 for just the food, no drinks, and everything was worth it. Great experience overall!

First visit. Atmosphere was pleasant and comfortable. Plenty of tv‚Äôs. Service was friendly. Had appetizers of fried pickles, pretzel bites and chips /salsa. All were good.
Restroom clean.
Boneless wings were tasty and plenty of chicken. Wife had steak that was cooked to her order but not outstanding in flavor. I had triple decker sandwich. It was huge and flavorful. Couldn‚Äôt eat it all. Tater tots were crispy.
We intend to rerun some day but the experience wasn‚Äôt exceptional.
Mac bowls are to DIE for. It brought a tear to my eye tasting it. Best you‚Äôll have. There appetizers like the cheese balls are SO good and everything about this place is AMAZING

Recently dined at Iron City Sports Bar and had a great experience. Ordered 10 boneless wings with chipotle BBQ and sweet house hot flavors, and 15 bone-in wings with mango habanero and sweet house hot. Both were generously sized and sauced perfectly. The Staff was friendly, especially with my son, and service was prompt. The atmosphere is relaxed with ample seating and plenty of TVs for sports enthusiasts. Clean facilities and overall, a top-notch spot.

I‚Äôm not a fan of sports bars, but our group decided to have dinner here. The service was  incredibly slow. From the time we arrived until our food was served was about 90 minutes. One in our group didn‚Äôt get served until everyone else was finished eating. Although the food was good, it wasn‚Äôt worth the wait.

detailedReviews.author: John Darnell
detailedReviews.text: First time being back since they first open. The staff was great got seated right away then the waiter was right there taking drink orders. I ordered wings and garlic parm fries. Wife got the burger with the pulled pork on it. everything came out hot and fresh with great taste. There was a couple downside my wings came out needing a life jacket way to much sauce. Plus for being a sit down restaurant it would of been nice to have actual silverware instead of pre packaged plastic silverware. Will definitely be back.

detailedReviews.author: Jody Carroll
detailedReviews.text: Terrible service was the theme. Apparently we came at a bad time (shift change) as I was reaching over the bar to retrieve napkins and asking for dinnerware after food was served. Seen plenty of employees including management and not a single hello, how was the service, hope to see you again, or thanks for visiting. Food was basic except for the burger (thumbs up). Thank goodness for the company I had with me it made the experience memorable.

detailedReviews.author: Matthew Trivits
detailedReviews.text:
This place is a bunch of missed opportunity and mediocrity. This may be a personal taste thing FWIW, but the wings have that fried non breaded greasy thing going similar to roosters but not as good. I'll give them that, i have certain taste for wings.

But the nachos are disgraceful. $11 for a plate of tortilla chips with cold meat, cold beans, cold cheese and sour cream. The pico was old or canned or something. It was a 4 dollar item if I'm being generous. A nit pick here, but fresh jalape√±os are the only way. Pickled jalape√±os are for barbecue and sandwiches.

The nachos really show the laziness. Nachos are a low cost, low labor item. It's all markup for the business. That's an opportunity. Blow me away with your nachos. The nachos absolutely kept me from ordering an entree. If you're going to do these I suggest doing some recon at other restaurants. Meat beans and chips should be hot and the corners toasty. Drizzle with hot cheese. Then pile on top some fresh pico, cilantro, lime wedges and salsa Verde. Dollop o daisy on top and bobs your uncle.

Another nit pick, learn how to pour Guinness.

I harp on this because I want to help, I want to like iron city I love the legacy and nostalgia of the ol wingers building. But I feel like I get fleeced overtime I go.

You're running an eatery in a competitive market. I'm sitting at your table, you have my audience, just keep up your end of the bargain and keep me entertained! It's not hard.

detailedReviews.text: Worst experience I‚Äôve had! We started out with Buckeye Bites as an appetizer and they were very dark and hard.   My Carolina gold wings were good.  The loaded tots were very overcooked and did not taste well at all.  My drink was so watered down and inappropriately mixed that the overall taste left it undrinkable.  But the worse thing was the steak.   Upon recieving it the smell hit our entire table immediately.   Thinking it may have just been the onions my fianc√© cut into it and the rotten smell immediately made us all nauseas. The best thing about this meal was the ice water.  Will NOT be returning especially for the price!  If I could give a zero star rating I would!

detailedReviews.author: Paul Bisson
detailedReviews.text: I mostly get food for take out from Iron City since I originally tried it during Covid and found I really enjoyed their food. I can say there have been times when I have eaten in restaurant that I should have gone elsewhere because the meal took so long to come out we had to just take it to go and get in the car to not be late going somewhere. Generally giving yourself two hours at a restaurant to order food, eat, and leave should be ample time. Hopefully that has been resolved since we last experienced that.

detailedReviews.author: Me Here
detailedReviews.text: Despite all the bad reviews about their customer service I ordered carryout and found the complaints valid. Ordered 10 dry rub and 10 hot wings. No wings had sauce and were mixed in the box. Neither were hot. Neither had much flavor. The girl on the phone was super slow and when I picked up my order she obviously didn't care. She also asked me if I wanted celery but they didn't give it to me. I am local but they are 2 for messing up my orders. Don't know how they stay in business.

detailedReviews.author: HunE Bunny
detailedReviews.text: Atmosphere was nice and staff at entry very friendly. Our server was nice, but she hardly came back checking on us and my hubs had to wait for a long time to ask for a refill. I felt like she was rushing us when she came back w our check. The food was good- I had the Iron City Burger w fries & my hubs had boneless wings. Hubs said his wings (spicy garlic, I think) were good, taste of chicken was good on but he said it could be more spicy. My burger was tasty but fries were a little too salty. The burger was really yummy BUT when we got home.... I rushed to the bathroom getting sick-doesn't taste good coming back up!!! So, I don't think we will be going back for a while!!
